<p style="text-align: center; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold;">For more information or to book our Twin Centre Holidays &amp; Tours please call 01483 79 11 11</p>
<p>Experience the true beauty of the mountains on this 14 night holiday to France and Switzerland, taking in two famous resorts in awe inspiring settings, and including a spectacular train journey across the Alps on the ‘Mont Blanc Express’ route. A great value way to discover the best of the Alps, you will stay in two of our comfortable and welcoming partner hotels, with Inghams reps on hand to ensure you have a memorable experience and to recommend the best walks and excursions.</p>
<p>Please note: From 3rd April to 24 June 2017, the Mont Blanc Express railway service from Chamonix to Châtelard-Frontière (Swiss border) is closed to allow the installation of a new rail operation system. All Mont Blanc Express trains will be replaced by shuttle service between Saint-Gervais and Le Chatelard Frontiere following the Mont Blanc Express timetable. From Le Chatelard the usual train service will operate as usual.</p>
<p><em>From 5th September to 30th November 2017, the Mont Blanc Express railway service from Argentiere to Montroc is closed to allow for rail improvements, this section of the route has a short distance usually lasting for 8 minutes on the train. All Mont Blanc Express trains will be replaced by shuttle service. From Montroc the usual train schedule will operate as usual.</em></p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Itinerary</h2>
<p><strong>DAYS 1-7</strong><br />Start your holiday in the iconic village of <a data-udi="umb://document/2735e2389f7c411cb3061226ce7548d1" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2735e2389f7c411cb3061226ce7548d1}" title="Chamonix"><strong>Chamonix</strong></a>. This lively resort is set right at the foot of the Mont Blanc, Europe’s highest mountain, and has endless opportunities for outdoor activities. Stay in the <a data-udi="umb://document/e1fdabc5ec6e4e7ca010e2a7d37451fe" href="/{localLink:umb://document/e1fdabc5ec6e4e7ca010e2a7d37451fe}" title="Hotel Pointe Isabelle"><strong>Hotel Pointe Isabelle</strong></a>, superbly located in the centre of Chamonix with wonderful views of Mont Blanc. The hotel is newly renovated in a comtemporary style with lots of references to the great Victorian British explorer Isabella Straton, after whom the hotel is named.</p>
<p><strong>DAY 8 MONT BLANC EXPRESS</strong><br />Transfer from Chamonix to Saas Fee, total journey time 3½ hours (unescorted). Start your journey on the ‘Mont Blanc Express’ train from Chamonix to Martigny, before joining the Swiss Rail network to Visp, and finally a scenic bus ride up to traffic free Saas Fee. The journey has magnificent views throughout and will take you right through the heart of the mountains. Trains are comfortable and you can enjoy the views and relax on board. Upgrade to 1st Class on the Martigny-Visp train for £33, (no 1st class seats on Mont Blanc Express).</p>
<p><strong>DAYS 8-14 </strong><br />Arrive in <a data-udi="umb://document/ae93f514436f422b8a051f43d7310e8e" href="/{localLink:umb://document/ae93f514436f422b8a051f43d7310e8e}" title="Saas Fee"><strong>Saas Fee</strong></a>, your Hotel is a short stroll from the bus terminal. Saas Fee is known as Switzerland’s ‘Pearl of the Alps’. Full of traditional charm, this traffic-free village is set high in the Valais region with fantastic walking opportunities and spectacular views all round. The <a data-udi="umb://document/aabbb2d3cc864d7e919c0af2d8191af7" href="/{localLink:umb://document/aabbb2d3cc864d7e919c0af2d8191af7}" title="Hotel Europa"><strong>Hotel Europa</strong></a> has good facilities, with a spa and excellent views of the mountains.</p>
</div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>What’s included</h2>
<ul>
<li>Return flights from UK (flight supplements may apply)</li>
<li>Airport coach transfers to Chamonix and rail/bus transfers from Saas Fee</li>
<li>14 nights en suite accommodation</li>
<li>Daily buffet breakfast</li>
<li>3 course evening meals (7 days a week) with a glass of wine or beer included </li>
<li>Free daily packed lunch included for your stay at the Hotel Europa in Saas Fee </li>
<li>Scenic Rail journey on the ‘Mont Blanc Express’</li>
<li>Services of Inghams Reps in each resort (not on rail journey)</li>
<li><strong>Free</strong> Saas-Fee resort card included</li>
<li><strong>Free</strong> use of lifts, cable-cars and buses to local villages in Saas Valley</li>
<li><strong>Free</strong> Chamonix resort card includes FREE bus and train travel in the Chamonix valley and reductions on many more services</li>
<li><strong>Free</strong> HALF-PRICE travel card included for all excursions and travel in Switzerland</li>
<li><strong>Free</strong> luggage transfer between the <strong>Hotel Pointe Isabelle</strong> and the <strong>Hotel Europa</strong></li>
</ul>
<p>Please refer to relevant resort pages for descriptions of all hotels and resorts. All optional excursions in <strong>Chamonix</strong> and <strong>Saas Fee</strong> are bookable locally via your Representatives.</p>
</div>
<div><em>Please note that we act at all times as selling agent for the suppliers of activities &amp; excursions. See our <a href="/{localLink:66d6dfd2-b127-48e8-b6d8-228d6e59ea65}" title="Terms &amp; Conditions">t</a><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/legal/terms-conditions">erms &amp; conditions</a>. Hotels are subject to change, but will always be of the same standard.</em></div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Accommodation</h2>
<p><strong>Chamonix</strong><br /><a data-udi="umb://document/e1fdabc5ec6e4e7ca010e2a7d37451fe" href="/{localLink:umb://document/e1fdabc5ec6e4e7ca010e2a7d37451fe}" title="Hotel Pointe Isabelle">Hotel Pointe Isabelle</a> ***</p>
<p><strong>Saas Fee</strong><br /><a data-udi="umb://document/aabbb2d3cc864d7e919c0af2d8191af7" href="/{localLink:umb://document/aabbb2d3cc864d7e919c0af2d8191af7}" title="Hotel Europa">Hotel Europa</a> ***</p>
</div>
